<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>{{ title | default('Cyclistic Data Analysis') }}</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ url_for('static', filename='styles.css') }}">
</head>
<body>
    <div id="top"></div>

    <div class="container">
        <nav class="main-nav">
            <ul>
                <li><a href="{{ url_for('index') }}">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="{{ url_for('summary') }}">Summary</a></li>
                <li><a href="{{ url_for('data') }}">Data Visualization</a></li>
                <li><a href="{{ url_for('map_view') }}">Map</a></li>
                <li><a href="{{ url_for('recommend') }}">Recommendations</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>

        <main> 
            {% block content %}
            <section class="summary-container">
                <h2>Cyclistic Analysis Project by James Masland</h2>
                <p>
                    This is a capstone project for my Data Analytics certificate. 
                    It has been an invaluable learning experience and highlights the skills that set me apart.
                    It is hosted on my website as a Flask application.
                    Based on real world Divvy historical data in Chicago.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The analysis enhances Cyclistic's marketing strategy by examining the distinct usage patterns of members versus casual riders. 
                    The project answers three key questions that will guide the future marketing program.
                </p>

                <div class="key-insights">
                    <ul>
                        <li>How do annual members and casual riders use Cyclistic bikes differently?</li>
                        <li>Why would casual riders buy Cyclistic annual memberships?</li>
                        <li>How can Cyclistic use digital media to influence casual riders to become members?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <h3>Report Deliverables</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>A clear statement of the business task</li>
                    <li>A description of all data sources used</li>
                    <li>Documentation of any cleaning or manipulation of data</li>
                    <li>A summary of your analysis</li>
                    <li>Supporting visualizations and key findings</li>
                    <li>Your top three recommendations based on your analysis</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Data Information</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>12 monthly CSV reports (Sep 2023 - Aug 2024)</li>
                    <li><a href="https://divvy-tripdata.s3.amazonaws.com/index.html" target="_blank">Link to Divvy Data Source</a></li>
                    <li>5,699,639 total rows analyzed</li>
                    <li>Consolidated and cleaned using DuckDB</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Data Integrity</h3>
                <p>
                    Rows containing these outliers were filtered out before analysis:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Negative Durations:</strong> 344</li>
                    <li><strong>Longer Than 3 Hours:</strong> 21,988</li>
                    <li><strong>Shorter Than 1 Minute:</strong> 129,849</li>
                    <li><strong>Distances greater than 25 km:</strong> 157</li>
                    <li><strong>Missing Location:</strong> 7526</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Data Limitations</h3>
                <p>
                    The analysis is constrained by the lack of specific information, including bike ID, ride path, and pricing. The following limitations were identified:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Distance:</strong> We only have the start and end points so we cannot know the true distances.
                    <li><strong>Lost Bikes:</strong> Instances of lost bikes cannot be confirmed.</li>
                    <li><strong>Membership Cost:</strong> The perceived value of membership pricing remains undetermined.</li>
                    <li><strong>Ride Cost:</strong> It is unknown whether current ride costs are set to encourage membership.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Database Columns</h3>
                <table class="narrow-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Column Name</th>
                            <th>Description</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>ride_id</strong></td>
                            <td>Unique identifier for each ride</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>rideable_type</strong></td>
                            <td>Type of rideable vehicle (electric/classic)</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>started_at</strong></td>
                            <td>Timestamp when the ride started</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>ended_at</strong></td>
                            <td>Timestamp when the ride ended</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>start_station_name</strong></td>
                            <td>Name of the station where the ride started</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>start_station_id</strong></td>
                            <td>Unique identifier for the starting station</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>end_station_name</strong></td>
                            <td>Name of the station where the ride ended</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>end_station_id</strong></td>
                            <td>Unique identifier for the ending station</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>start_lat</strong></td>
                            <td>Latitude of the starting location</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>start_lng</strong></td>
                            <td>Longitude of the starting location</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>end_lat</strong></td>
                            <td>Latitude of the ending location</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>end_lng</strong></td>
                            <td>Longitude of the ending location</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>member_casual</strong></td>
                            <td>Indicates if the rider is a member or a casual user</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </section>
            {% endblock %}
        </main>

        <footer class="site-footer">
            <div class="footer-content">
